    "We must examine individual item scores to assess specific program weaknesses.",
    "All items scored ≥4 (≥80%) out of 5, as show in Table 4, indicating no significant flaws requiring major modifications.",
    "Minor improvements we could make include adding testimonials from highly active individuals with chronic pain who learned to pace themselves and mentioning that lessons are preferably followed in order but can also be explored based on personal preferences after completing week 1.",
